This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) subfield of Computer Science, as it deals with automatic annotation of temporal expressions in text. Specifically, it involves converting older format resources to the TimeML/TIMEX3 format, which is a standard for temporal annotation in NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as using a TimeML annotation tool, which suggests that it could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Finally, the paper's focus on temporal expression recognition could also make it relevant to the sub-field of Computational Neuroscience, which deals with the study of the brain's temporal processing abilities. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
